Class TradingCardInventorySystemModel

java.lang.Object
TradingCardInventorySystemModel
public class TradingCardInventorySystemModel extends Object
The model component of the Trading Card Inventory System. Manages the core data structures and the logic for a trading card inventory, including the card collection, binders, and decks.

      public boolean removeCardFromBinder(Binder binder, Card card)

      true if removal was successful, false otherwise

    • executeTrade

      public boolean executeTrade(Binder binder, Card incoming, Card outgoing)
      Executes a trade by swapping an outgoing card with an incoming card in the binder. The incoming card will also be added to the collection with a count of 0; essentially, the incoming card gets its own new "slot" in the collection.
      Parameters:
      binder - The binder where the trade occurs.
      incoming - The card to be added, assumed to be outside the binder and collection
      outgoing - The card to be removed.
      Returns:
      true if the trade was successful, false otherwise.
